The MP, a millionaire from a former oil merchant, was first called upon to explain his issues in May when it emerged that he had claimed thousands of pounds for his garden, even before the finance authority approved it, that "it could be considered excessive".
One of the activists dug a pound-shaped pit in Mr Duncan's lawn in protest after it was revealed he had claimed 4,000 pounds over three years.
When asked about the mortgage increase last night, Mr. Duncan said, "It was due to the capital increase, which was approved by both the finance authority and Legg".
He added: "This is not a matter of concealment and clicking or breaking the rules or anything else.
It's absolutely straight down, by the rules, legitimate, and that's it.
