The subjects of geography and history will be strengthened as part of the reform of the general secondary school, Chatel said.
Education Minister Luc Chatel said in an interview with JDD on Sunday that history and geography subjects would be "enhanced" as part of the reform of general secondary schools, although their education will no longer be compulsory in the final year of the secondary school focusing on exact sciences.
Now all second-year students will have four hours a week and a common culture program for all, Chatel confirmed.
