A survey by Ifop, published by Humanité on Saturday, showed that seven out of 10 French people (69%) disagreed with the government's proposal to abolish compulsory history and geography lessons in the senior year with a specialisation of 'S', and many intellectuals and teachers criticized the abolishment, both on the left and some members of the right.
