In the Master's programme 2 (M2) they will take an entrance exam focused on their subject at the beginning of the year and another exam at the end of the year to verify their teaching ability, the Minister explained.
They will take part in internships during the second year of their Master's degree and will act as a trainee professor in the first year.
If you add up all the internships that you'll be offered before the admissions process, you'll gain more experience with students, almost 300 hours, he continued.
