Passive employee attitudes can lead to deadly demoralization.
Suicides at France Telecom, PSA or Renault are only a visible part of a much more widespread general phenomenon that affects mainly management.
This demobilization has a negative impact on the development of all the intellectual functions of society, including research and development, and more importantly, economic intelligence.
Indeed, the EI 'requires an active approach and a predictive capacity from all stakeholders' and requires commitments from employees that are completely contrary to the revenues of authoritarian management.
