And finally, because most executives have a simplified view of human behavior.
Because they're graduates of engineering colleges, they have a mechanical interpretation of psychology.
For the sake of convenience, they are learning an old behavioural theory, now revived by "neuroscientists" from the United States and widely circulated without further knowledge by scientific institutions and the media.
