Identify and measure the mobilization factors.
On the contrary, the managerial revolution, necessary for the proper functioning of modern enterprises, involves the adoption of a final vision of human behavior.
It consists in integrating basic care into all management purposes and practices: Employees will only be able to commit to the company if they are seen as a clear means to achieve their dreams, ambitions and projects.
At present, only studies on motivational functional analysis deal with this concept of employee motivation.
These studies have shown that they evaluate their undertakings on the basis of a pre-defined document that allows them, through an image that reflects the undertaking, to evaluate what it offers them to achieve their life objectives.
